                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, but careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <date>19th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the donors; incipit of Text I
                           (fol.3r); titles and initial lines of the prayers to be read; directives
                           to the ministers; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals. 
 On the incipit page of Text I (fol. 3r) a few lines are
                           rubricated (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1va">ff. 1va-2</locus>
                           <desc>vb: Taʾammǝra ʾIyasus “Miracles of Jesus”: 1 miracles.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#66vb">f. 66vb</locus>
                           <desc>: Purchase note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#66vb">66vb</locus>: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘተ[ሣ]የጦ፡ በ፲ሽልንግ፡ በዘመነ፡
                              ንጉ&lt;ሥ፡ ኃ&gt;ይለ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወመስፍን፡ ራስ፡ ሥዩ&lt;ም፡&gt; ወጳጳስነ፡ ባስልዮ&lt;ስ፡&gt;
                              ፵&lt;…&gt; የካቲት፡ &lt;…&gt; አለቃ፡ ረዳ፡ &lt;…&gt;</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> Some words of the note have been erased. The note
                           mentions that the Ms. was bought for 10 shillings (šǝlǝng) during the
                           time of King Ḫāyla Śǝllāse I (1930-74), Metropolitan Basǝlyos (in tenure
                           in 1948-70) and rās<note> Śǝyyum Mängäša, (governor of Tǝgray in
                              1947-60). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Crude notes written in pen: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 47v.
 - Crude note written in pen in the upper
                           margin: <locus from="63v" to="64r">63v-64r</locus>, 65v-66r.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings are indicated by the names of the
                              weekdays written in the upper margin: ዘሰኑይ: <locus target="#1r">fol.
                                 1r</locus>. ዘሰሉስ: <locus target="#11r">fol. 11r</locus>. ዘረቡዕ:
                                 <locus target="#18r">fol. 18r</locus>. ዘሐሙስ: <locus target="#22v">fol. 22v</locus>. ዘዘወትር: <locus target="#27v">fol. 27v</locus>.
                              ዘሐሙስ: <locus target="#30v">fol. 30v</locus>. ዘዓርብ: <locus target="#33r">fol. 33r</locus>. ዘቀዳም: <locus target="#40r">fol.
                                 40r</locus>. ዘእሁድ: <locus target="#46r">fol. 46r</locus>. ዘዘወትር:
                                 <locus target="#55r">fol. 55r</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
